import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Miles_per_Gallon'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Displacement'], data['Weight_in_lbs'], c=data['Cylinders'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Displacement')
    ax.set_ylabel('Weight_in_lbs')
    ax.set_title('How does the weight of the cars vary with their engine size (Displacement)?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Cylinders")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
